    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 is the applicable regulatory standard and the single test condition is the only clinically relevant configuration for this submission. Validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) are satisfied for all three primary QoIs. Overall model credibility is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
